_:Be8b4fc9ca665965692dd1bf45dd9008e <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "It (the hypophysis) develops embryonically in all vertebrates from two ectodermal evaginations that meet and unite. (...) A well-developed hypophyseal system with functional connections to the hypothalamus is unique to craniates.[well established][VHOG]" .
